radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild atelectasis at the lung bases; liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesions; patent portal venous system; normal gallbladder; normal spleen and adrenal glands; normal pancreas; symmetric nephrograms in kidneys; normal ureters; mild dilation of distal appendix measuring 12 mm with minimal adjacent fat stranding; no hydronephrosis; normal abdominal aorta; normal bladder; no pelvic lymphadenopathy; no free pelvic fluid; thin ovaries with follicular activity; no focal lytic or sclerotic lesions in osseous structures.
